{The core principle here is that a *larger* ratio – where the model’s repetition is significantly less than the repetition given the ground truth prefix – indicates *better* performance in minimizing repetition. {This is because it demonstrates that the model is more effectively avoiding self-reference and generating novel sequences.}}

